They suffered the
Reagan Revolution,

00:56:55.970 --> 00:56:59.180
wherein investment in
the criminal justice

00:56:59.180 --> 00:57:04.370
system in prison
succeeded that on schools.

00:57:04.370 --> 00:57:07.261
Today, a lot of
Americans are starting

00:57:07.261 --> 00:57:09.760
to send their kids to private
school, fancy private schools.

00:57:09.760 --> 00:57:12.850
I know some friends here.

00:57:12.850 --> 00:57:15.550
So if you've gutted
out your public school

00:57:15.550 --> 00:57:18.270
system, that means
social mobility is gone,

00:57:18.270 --> 00:57:19.800
jobs are gone.

00:57:19.800 --> 00:57:22.130
You can, of course,
become a barista.

00:57:22.130 --> 00:57:23.650
But better jobs
are not available.

00:57:23.650 --> 00:57:27.980
So you know, there was
this entire abandonment

00:57:27.980 --> 00:57:32.060
all of the economic interests,
of large numbers of people.

00:57:32.060 --> 00:57:33.980
So the left moved to the right.

00:57:33.980 --> 00:57:37.560
And it's only recently
that the left has

00:57:37.560 --> 00:57:39.410
started swinging left again.

00:57:39.410 --> 00:57:41.850
But now Marx is dead.

00:57:41.850 --> 00:57:42.730
All right?

00:57:42.730 --> 00:57:45.620
There is no counterpoint,
so they're confused.

00:57:45.620 --> 00:57:47.130
They don't know what they want.

00:57:47.130 --> 00:57:50.360
So the left is in complete
confusion anywhere you look.

00:57:50.360 --> 00:57:52.170
Look at England.

00:57:52.170 --> 00:57:53.310
Jeremy Corbyn.

00:57:53.310 --> 00:57:57.590
He has no idea of
what he believes in.

00:57:57.590 --> 00:57:59.590
Right?

00:57:59.590 --> 00:58:04.420
So the entire politicking, the
opposition, to David Cameron

00:58:04.420 --> 00:58:05.720
came from his own party.

00:58:05.720 --> 00:58:08.810
It was Boris Johnson
who sank Cameron's boat,

00:58:08.810 --> 00:58:11.810
not of course, the
wonderful opposition leader.

00:58:11.810 --> 00:58:13.530
So the left is lost.

00:58:13.530 --> 00:58:16.800
The left, in the memorable
words of a friend who's

00:58:16.800 --> 00:58:21.930
a young politician, said
the left has been left out.

00:58:21.930 --> 00:58:23.690
So left doesn't
even know who it is.

00:58:23.690 --> 00:58:26.770
So I think the left is sort of
starting to figure things out,

00:58:26.770 --> 00:58:30.050
and has moved to the-- it's
starting to gravitate back

00:58:30.050 --> 00:58:31.500
again under Bernie Sanders.

00:58:31.500 --> 00:58:34.510
But I don't think it's
moved to the right at all.

00:58:34.510 --> 00:58:36.840
And I think what has happened
is that the right has

00:58:36.840 --> 00:58:39.570
moved extreme right.

00:58:39.570 --> 00:58:42.310
The center of gravity
started tending

00:58:42.310 --> 00:58:44.340
towards far too much insanity.

00:58:44.340 --> 00:58:45.560
I mean, look at Ted Cruz.

00:58:45.560 --> 00:58:48.590
He makes Donald Trump look good.

00:58:48.590 --> 00:58:50.680
I mean, pull up the
video, and watch his video

00:58:50.680 --> 00:58:54.960
on machine gun bacon, where he
cooks bacon on a machine gun.

00:58:54.960 --> 00:58:57.140
He fires until it becomes hot.

00:58:57.140 --> 00:59:02.610
And you know, it's a
wonderfully incongruous sight

00:59:02.610 --> 00:59:08.050
to see a chubby middle-aged
man act very macho.

00:59:08.050 --> 00:59:11.290
I mean, I would much
rather he ran a triathlon

00:59:11.290 --> 00:59:13.280
to show me how fit he was.

00:59:13.280 --> 00:59:15.530
But no, he's appealing
to something very deep.

00:59:15.530 --> 00:59:16.930
So what is happening?

00:59:16.930 --> 00:59:20.170
But now, what is happening is
that the economics of the right

00:59:20.170 --> 00:59:20.890
are turning left.

00:59:20.890 --> 00:59:22.500
So it's a very confused time.

00:59:22.500 --> 00:59:24.590
AUDIENCE: Sir, I
think when you're

00:59:24.590 --> 00:59:26.955
looking at fascism
and all these movement

00:59:26.955 --> 00:59:29.350
in history, you're kind
of a little bit scratching

00:59:29.350 --> 00:59:32.505
the surface, making fun of
Italian maybe, and Hitler,

00:59:32.505 --> 00:59:33.270
and his mustache.

00:59:33.270 --> 00:59:37.030
But really, those are like,
counter-revolutionary movements

00:59:37.030 --> 00:59:39.435
against what was happening
in Soviet Russia,

00:59:39.435 --> 00:59:42.117
and there was a moment of
restructuring for capitalism

00:59:42.117 --> 00:59:43.280
worldwide.

00:59:43.280 --> 00:59:46.720
So I think what is really
key is the economic situation

00:59:46.720 --> 00:59:48.780
in the world that
we should look at,

00:59:48.780 --> 00:59:51.840
instead of just looking at Ted
Cruz and how ridiculous it is.

00:59:51.840 --> 00:59:53.650
So I think the key
here is inequality,

00:59:53.650 --> 00:59:59.750
and it was one of your
three like, main points,

00:59:59.750 --> 01:00:01.197
but I think it is
the main point.

01:00:01.197 --> 01:00:03.030
So I want to know what
you think about that.

01:00:03.030 --> 01:00:06.030
ATUL SINGH: It's a
very valid point.

01:00:06.030 --> 01:00:08.540
Yes, inequality is key.

01:00:08.540 --> 01:00:14.480
But remember that the
Nazi party and, let's say,

01:00:14.480 --> 01:00:16.870
Italian fascists, were
strange in the sense they

01:00:16.870 --> 01:00:18.660
were counter-revolutionaries.

01:00:18.660 --> 01:00:21.840
But in some ways, they
were also revolutionaries.

01:00:21.840 --> 01:00:26.240
Because the Nazi Party was not
the upper class Prussian Junker

01:00:26.240 --> 01:00:28.850
class.

01:00:28.850 --> 01:00:29.840
Let's be very clear.

01:00:29.840 --> 01:00:32.800
The Prussian Junker class
suffered under the Nazis.

01:00:32.800 --> 01:00:36.240
The aristocrats often got the
boot, often with their lives.

01:00:36.240 --> 01:00:41.220
It was a lower middle
class, petty bourgeoisie.

01:00:41.220 --> 01:00:43.140
The lower middle
class that wanted

01:00:43.140 --> 01:00:45.840
to keep the upper classes and
take power themselves-- it

01:00:45.840 --> 01:00:47.020
was a power grab.

01:00:47.020 --> 01:00:49.260
But they didn't want the
workers, their workers,

01:00:49.260 --> 01:00:50.610
to take over power.

01:00:50.610 --> 01:00:51.780
So it's a little complex.

01:00:51.780 --> 01:00:53.460
You see what I am getting at?

01:00:53.460 --> 01:00:55.370
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:00:55.370 --> 01:00:57.065
ATUL SINGH: Pardon me?

01:00:57.065 --> 01:00:57.940
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:00:57.940 --> 01:00:59.040
ATUL SINGH: Pardon me?

01:00:59.040 --> 01:00:59.915
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:01:03.270 --> 01:01:05.810
ATUL SINGH: It was a
power grab certainly.

01:01:05.810 --> 01:01:07.290
And certain classes flourished.

01:01:07.290 --> 01:01:10.730
But parts of the old
elite got wiped out too.

01:01:10.730 --> 01:01:13.579
AUDIENCE: A capitalistic
restructuring, right?

01:01:13.579 --> 01:01:14.370
ATUL SINGH: Partly.

01:01:14.370 --> 01:01:15.949
But it was not
entirely capitalistic,

01:01:15.949 --> 01:01:17.240
because the state was involved.

01:01:17.240 --> 01:01:19.170
It was collectivist as well.

01:01:19.170 --> 01:01:20.349
It's complicated.

01:01:20.349 --> 01:01:22.890
That's what I'm trying to get,
is the state, the bureaucrats,

01:01:22.890 --> 01:01:24.310
were very heavily involved.

01:01:24.310 --> 01:01:26.950
And I think you're right.

01:01:26.950 --> 01:01:28.330
Economics is key.

01:01:28.330 --> 01:01:31.930
A long time ago, someone said
it's the economy's stupid.

01:01:31.930 --> 01:01:34.820
And that's part of
the answer, for sure.

01:01:34.820 --> 01:01:38.850
But economics is not all,
because you can not just

01:01:38.850 --> 01:01:41.090
have growth, and
things will be all OK,

01:01:41.090 --> 01:01:42.510
as China has demonstrated.

01:01:42.510 --> 01:01:44.740
But at the same time,
if you have no growth,

01:01:44.740 --> 01:01:47.670
and you're like France, you're
stuck in over 10% unemployment

01:01:47.670 --> 01:01:50.800
since 1980, and you've
got massive unemployment

01:01:50.800 --> 01:01:53.130
in your [INAUDIBLE],
which is where you've

01:01:53.130 --> 01:01:57.701
got all these Arab kids
unemployed and unemployable,

01:01:57.701 --> 01:01:59.200
then they start
getting radicalized,

01:01:59.200 --> 01:02:00.950
as you can see on
the Cote d'Azur.

01:02:00.950 --> 01:02:03.670
Cote d'Azur, which is a
place where the rich stay,

01:02:03.670 --> 01:02:07.020
is also a place where the
radicals come and flourish.

01:02:07.020 --> 01:02:08.170
And the radicals grow.

01:02:08.170 --> 01:02:08.870
So it's complex.

01:02:08.870 --> 01:02:12.040
But I agree that you
have to figure out

01:02:12.040 --> 01:02:15.240
how do people find jobs and
how do people earn a living?

01:02:15.240 --> 01:02:17.610
If they cannot, if we
have so much automation,

01:02:17.610 --> 01:02:20.740
then maybe it's time to think
seriously about what Keynes

01:02:20.740 --> 01:02:21.240
said.

01:02:21.240 --> 01:02:27.610
Maybe we should all be writing
poetry and debating philosophy.

01:02:27.610 --> 01:02:30.880
Build a greater sort
of Athenian Republic,

01:02:30.880 --> 01:02:33.910
now that we don't need slaves,
we can have robots instead.

01:02:33.910 --> 01:02:36.690
AUDIENCE: This question is not
about the global far right,

01:02:36.690 --> 01:02:41.270
but instead about the media.

01:02:41.270 --> 01:02:42.990
And it's rather an
incongruous time

01:02:42.990 --> 01:02:47.180
to be setting up a
media organization,

01:02:47.180 --> 01:02:50.360
and particularly with
the likes of Google News

01:02:50.360 --> 01:02:52.780
to compete with, for example.

01:02:52.780 --> 01:02:56.480
I wondered if you
could comment on what

01:02:56.480 --> 01:03:06.190
you see as what's necessary in
terms of the evolution of media

01:03:06.190 --> 01:03:10.654
going forward, and how "Fair
Observer" fits into that.

01:03:10.654 --> 01:03:11.570
ATUL SINGH: Thank you.

01:03:11.570 --> 01:03:14.750
Thank you for that question.

01:03:14.750 --> 01:03:16.720
That's an almost
entirely different talk.

01:03:16.720 --> 01:03:19.010
I gave a talk at MIT
earlier this year.

01:03:19.010 --> 01:03:24.900
And that was on the rule of the
fourth estate in the New New

01:03:24.900 --> 01:03:25.710
World.

01:03:25.710 --> 01:03:27.910
And the New New
World is a riff off

01:03:27.910 --> 01:03:29.970
from Michael Lewis's
book about the internet.

01:03:29.970 --> 01:03:33.520
And fourth estate is what
Edmund Burke, an Englishman,

01:03:33.520 --> 01:03:36.790
called the press,
which was sitting

01:03:36.790 --> 01:03:38.920
in the Parliament
for the first time

01:03:38.920 --> 01:03:41.880
and watching the three estates--
the royals, the clergy,

01:03:41.880 --> 01:03:43.140
and the commons.

01:03:43.140 --> 01:03:48.840
And so we have lots of blogs and
lots of noise on the internet.

01:03:48.840 --> 01:03:50.200
That's one.

01:03:50.200 --> 01:03:54.070
And we have huge
media conglomerations,

01:03:54.070 --> 01:03:56.210
which through mergers
and acquisitions

01:03:56.210 --> 01:04:00.550
have become concentrated
in basically

01:04:00.550 --> 01:04:04.550
numbers that you could
count at most on two hands.

01:04:04.550 --> 01:04:07.930
And so, a monopoly of sorts,
or an oligopoly of sorts.

01:04:07.930 --> 01:04:10.760
And the profit-driven
model in the US

01:04:10.760 --> 01:04:14.750
means that everyone's
chasing the headline,

01:04:14.750 --> 01:04:16.580
and you have a
dumbing down of news,

01:04:16.580 --> 01:04:18.190
and attention spans
have gone down.

01:04:18.190 --> 01:04:20.090
And so, discourse has vanished.

01:04:20.090 --> 01:04:23.850
I'm of the firm belief--
not opinion, but belief--

01:04:23.850 --> 01:04:25.710
that democracy needs discourse.

01:04:25.710 --> 01:04:28.500
If you don't have discourse,
you won't have democracy.

01:04:28.500 --> 01:04:31.520
And so why am I setting this up?

01:04:31.520 --> 01:04:33.210
We are a nonprofit for a reason.

01:04:33.210 --> 01:04:37.330
I don't want to be beholden
to a venture capitalist who

01:04:37.330 --> 01:04:38.820
has a target on
my back and says,

01:04:38.820 --> 01:04:43.950
hey, why aren't we at 5
million uniques a month by now?

01:04:43.950 --> 01:04:53.620
So my idea of a media
organization now,

01:04:53.620 --> 01:04:56.740
particularly with the change
in political circumstances,

01:04:56.740 --> 01:04:58.810
is that it has got
to be independent.

01:04:58.810 --> 01:04:59.950
It has got to be fair.

01:04:59.950 --> 01:05:01.290
It has got to be diverse.

01:05:01.290 --> 01:05:02.850
It has got to be truthful.

01:05:02.850 --> 01:05:04.370
It has got to be credible.

01:05:04.370 --> 01:05:13.040
It has got to have this
identity that brings together

01:05:13.040 --> 01:05:14.830
people across cultures.

01:05:14.830 --> 01:05:19.680
And yes, it is hard competing
against Google News.

01:05:19.680 --> 01:05:24.730
Yes, it is hard
targeting people,

01:05:24.730 --> 01:05:27.690
and getting them to read
in-depth about, let's say,

01:05:27.690 --> 01:05:31.800
Turkey, and examine it
historical or philosophically.

01:05:31.800 --> 01:05:34.680
But where I see "Fair
Observer," frankly,

01:05:34.680 --> 01:05:40.310
as this New Age
intelligent readers,

01:05:40.310 --> 01:05:44.130
or intelligent audience's home,
where people are cosmopolitan,

01:05:44.130 --> 01:05:47.670
people have an interest
in issues of importance,

01:05:47.670 --> 01:05:49.830
people are globally
minded, where

01:05:49.830 --> 01:05:54.640
people are willing to question
assumptions, where people want

01:05:54.640 --> 01:05:57.850
to be informed, and educated,
and in turn, informally

01:05:57.850 --> 01:05:59.190
educate others.

01:05:59.190 --> 01:06:04.010
And it is very much in keeping
with the great tradition

01:06:04.010 --> 01:06:06.480
of, let's say, Benjamin Franklin
running his own newspaper,

01:06:06.480 --> 01:06:10.650
or Gandhi running his paper,
or any of the leading lights.

01:06:10.650 --> 01:06:15.260
And the funnel is really wide.

01:06:15.260 --> 01:06:16.750
You can see wild too.

01:06:16.750 --> 01:06:18.620
And the filter is really strong.

01:06:18.620 --> 01:06:21.340
So everything goes through
a quality check, and a fact

01:06:21.340 --> 01:06:22.680
check, and a language check.

01:06:22.680 --> 01:06:27.610
And what we aim to
be is independent.

01:06:27.610 --> 01:06:30.470
And that requires donations
from some of our readers,

01:06:30.470 --> 01:06:31.010
if not all.

01:06:31.010 --> 01:06:34.440
That requires grants from
certain organizations.

01:06:34.440 --> 01:06:36.270
That requires philanthropy.

01:06:36.270 --> 01:06:38.200
That requires
over-time monetizing

01:06:38.200 --> 01:06:42.290
through various
activities, whether it

01:06:42.290 --> 01:06:44.230
is organizing events,
or conferences,

01:06:44.230 --> 01:06:49.140
or selling premium
subscriptions,

01:06:49.140 --> 01:06:52.540
or for that matter,
doing workshops,

01:06:52.540 --> 01:06:54.332
delving into the
education space.

01:06:54.332 --> 01:06:56.040
Because one of the
things that is lacking

01:06:56.040 --> 01:06:59.490
is this civic education--
looking at things in context,

01:06:59.490 --> 01:07:03.170
looking at things across time.

01:07:03.170 --> 01:07:05.210
And that is why one
of the things we do

01:07:05.210 --> 01:07:07.780
is the Voices of the World
Program, where we go and train

01:07:07.780 --> 01:07:10.490
people how to critically,
express themselves

01:07:10.490 --> 01:07:13.670
clearly, and engage with the
great issues of our time.

01:07:13.670 --> 01:07:17.360
And with that, I think I've
come to the end of my time.

01:07:17.360 --> 01:07:18.630
Thank you so, so much.

01:07:18.630 --> 01:07:20.005
You've been a
wonderful audience.

01:07:20.005 --> 01:07:20.830
Thank you.

01:07:20.830 --> 01:07:24.480
[APPLAUSE]

